repo_interim_justification: The entire commit log, including interim commits and versions, is preserved going back to the beginning and with digital signatures. Every batch of commits is versioned and identifiable at runt-time.
repo_distributed_justification: Repository on GitHub, which uses git. git is distributed.
version_unique_justification:
Every batch of commits increments the version number, expressed as a single integer. Example: https://github.com/boostorg/beast/commit/1ca690db0615a170c155683968071ee9eb609bc0

Furthermore, when there is a Boost release, that release has its own Boost version, and the version of Beast at the time that the Boost snapshot was made becomes the version of Beast included in Boost.
version_tags_justification: Beast inherits the version of the Boost release it appears in, e.g.: https://github.com/boostorg/beast/tree/boost-1.68.0
release_notes_justification: In addition to https://github.com/boostorg/beast/blob/develop/CHANGELOG.md there are formatted, human readable release notes in the documentation:  https://www.boost.org/doc/libs/master/libs/beast/doc/html/beast/release_notes.html
